tionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>glover</i>, <i>gloifer</i> ‘glover; maker or seller of gloves’, a derivative of Old English <i>glōf</i> ‘glove’."],"variants":[{"name":"Glovier","meanings":["English (Worcestershire): variant of   Glover  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Gerald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>wald</i> ‘rule’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. There has been some confusion with   Gerard .  It died out in England at the end of the 13th century. However, it continued to be popular in Ireland, where it had been brought in the 12th century at the time of Strongbow's invasion. It was used in England in the 17th century and revived in the 19th century, along with several other long-extinct names of Norman, Old English, and Celtic origin, and is now more common than <i>Gerard</i>, which survived all along as an English ‘gentry’ name."],"variants":[{"name":"Jerrold","meanings":["Rare variant of   Gerald  , probably a transferred use of the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"Frank","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin. The name referred originally to a member of the tribe of the Franks, who are said to have got the name from a characteristic type of spear that they used. When the Franks migrated into Gaul in the 4th century, the country received its modern name of France (Late Latin <i>Francia</i>) and the tribal term Frank came to mean ‘Frenchman’. The name is now also used as a short form of   Francis   or   Franklin ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":39,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":48,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Gerald Frank Glover was born on 14 October 1175, in Warrington, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Chandra Jones. He died in 1225, in Dunster, Somerset, England, at the age of 50."},"et":{"14 October 1175–1225":"14. oktoober 1175–1225","1180–1230":"1180–1230","1197–1230":"1197–1230","1175–1225":"1175–1225","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","14 November 1197":"14. november 1197","1224":"1224","14 October 1175":"14. oktoober 1175","1175":"1175","1197":"1197","1230":"1230","1180":"1180","Gnosall, Staffordshire, England":"Gnosall, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dunster, Somerset, England":"Dunster, Somerset, England","Warrington, Buckinghamshire, England":"Warrington, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"14 October 1175–1225":"14. lokakuuta 1175–1225","1180–1230":"1180–1230","1197–1230":"1197–1230","1175–1225":"1175–1225","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","14 November 1197":"14. marraskuuta 1197","1224":"1224","14 October 1175":"14. lokakuuta 1175","1175":"1175","1197":"1197","1230":"1230","1180":"1180","Gnosall, Staffordshire, England":"Gnosall, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dunster, Somerset, England":"Dunster, Somerset, Englan